real_commentary: KICKOFF:  And we're off! Germany get us started. Strap in folks, this will be special.
our_sequence_commentary: [Kick Off] The Quarter-finals begin! Spain versus Germany in a highly anticipated clash.

real_commentary: SHOT!  Spain on the front foot immediately! Williams and Morata link up nicely, but Pedri's strike on the edge of the box is straight at Manuel Neuer. Now Cucurella is down...

real_commentary: The Chelsea man looks to have come off worse in a collision with Can, but he is OK to continue.

real_commentary: First bit of defending for Robin Le Normand but he deals with Sane well. Now Kroos scythes down Pedri as the Barcelona man tries to break.
our_sequence_commentary: [Injury] Early concern for Spain as Pedro González López is down with an injury.

real_commentary: Referee Anthony Taylor laying down the law early, demanding that all non-wearing armband players step away from him. Kroos remonstrated heavily there... not sure why. Fortunate not to be booked.
our_sequence_commentary: [Injury] Early concern for Germany as Manuel Neuer is down with an injury.

real_commentary: Now Gundogan brings down his former teammate Rodri. A bit feisty early on this one!
our_sequence_commentary: [Injury] Pedro González López (Spain) is down, receiving medical attention early in the match.

real_commentary: Now Gundogan brings down his former teammate Rodri. A bit feisty early on this one!

real_commentary: Pedri has already had awful luck with injuries in his career, and he does not look comfortable here. Dani Olmo getting ready as a distraught Pedri gingerly walks off. Have to feel for him.

real_commentary: This was the tackle that forced a disconsolate Pedri off. Looking back, how Kroos did not get a booking is astounding. There's no room for sentimentality in a Euros quarter-final Anthony Taylor!
our_sequence_commentary: [Injury] Injury concern for Spain as Nico Williams is down on the pitch.

real_commentary: This was the tackle that forced a disconsolate Pedri off. Looking back, how Kroos did not get a booking is astounding. There's no room for sentimentality in a Euros quarter-final Anthony Taylor!

real_commentary: End-to-end stuff now! This is what we came for. A promising Germany move breaks down before Spain steam down the other end of the pitch, but an ambitious Morata strike hits a white shirt.
our_sequence_commentary: [Shot Blocked] Attempt blocked. Álvaro Morata's right-footed shot from the right side of the box denied by Emre Can.

real_commentary: The hosts just showing a bit more attacking impetus now after Spain shaded a scrappy start. Just as I type that, Yamal makes a nice sliding interception and Spain have the ball back.

real_commentary: Kroos whips it in, and Tah rises highest, but he cannot leap high enough to get a decent connection and the ball rolls through to Simon.

real_commentary: YELLOW CARD!  Speaking of any means necessary, Le Normand is now booked for fouling Gundogan, and he is another one to miss any potential semi-final.
our_sequence_commentary: [Foul] Foul by Pau Torres (Spain) on Emre Can (Germany). Free kick in a promising position.

real_commentary: To stop Yamal, you have to kick Yamal. At least that's what Emre Can thinks. He avoids further punishment, though.

real_commentary: De la Fuente engaged in conversation with one of his lieutenants down on the sidelines. This one is still on a knife-edge.
our_sequence_commentary: [Foul] Foul by Rodri (Spain) on Toni Kroos (Germany) in midfield.

our_sequence_commentary: [Shot Missed] Attempt missed. Mikel Oyarzabal's left footed shot from the edge of the box goes wide.

real_commentary: YELLOW CARD!  Kroos is back on and Deniz Undav has been booked on the bench, presumably for dissent.
our_sequence_commentary: [General] Spain dominating possession with 75%, controlling play in their defensive third.

real_commentary: Kroos is still down receiving treatment - might Germany have to see this one out with 10 men?
our_sequence_commentary: [General] Spain dominating possession with 75%, controlling play in their defensive third.

real_commentary: This has been a forgettable extra-time period. Nacho now rolling around on the turf - not sure why.
our_sequence_commentary: [Injury] José Ignacio Fernández Iglesias (Spain) down with an injury, play halted.

real_commentary: This has been a forgettable extra-time period. Nacho now rolling around on the turf - not sure why.
our_sequence_commentary: [Injury] Manuel Neuer (Germany) down with an injury, play halted for treatment.

real_commentary: Oh dear. A very innocuous nudge from Wirtz sparked that reaction from Nacho. Surprise surprise, he's fine.
our_sequence_commentary: [Shot Saved] Attempt saved. Niclas Füllkrug's header from the centre of the box denied by Unai Simón.

real_commentary: SAVE!  Terrific save from Simon! Fullkrug bravely dives across Nacho's body for a diving header, but Simon springs to his right to deny the Dortmund man what would surely have been the winner.
our_sequence_commentary: [Shot Saved] Attempt saved. Niclas Füllkrug's header from the centre of the box denied by Unai Simón.

real_commentary: GOAL!  SPAIN 2-1 GERMANY (MERINO) WHAT WAS THAT ABOUT PENALTIES?!
our_sequence_commentary: [Goal] Goal! Spain 2, Germany 0. Mikel Merino heads in from the center of the box, assisted by Daniel Olmo.

real_commentary: GOAL!  Mikel Merino - the most unlikely hero - has surely just scored the goal that will send Germany out of the European Championships! The Sociedad midfielder is free to meet Olmo's cross, which he does with a majestic leap, and his header leaves Neuer rooted to the spot.
our_sequence_commentary: [Goal] Goal! Spain 2, Germany 0. Mikel Merino heads in from the center of the box, assisted by Daniel Olmo.

real_commentary: Counting down to the lottery of penalties now.
our_sequence_commentary: [Goal] Goal! Spain 2, Germany 0. Mikel Merino heads in from the center of the box, assisted by Daniel Olmo.

real_commentary: Germany have been given three minutes of injury time in extra time to conjure up another magic moment. Two have already been played. Spain defending for their lives.
our_sequence_commentary: [Shots] End-to-end action! Kimmich's effort blocked, then Ferrán Torres shoots wide from close range.

real_commentary: CLOSE!  And that might be that! Germany are patient, and a cross finds the head of Fullkrug - the man you want in that situation - but he heads wide!
our_sequence_commentary: [Shot Missed] Attempt missed. Niclas Füllkrug heads it over from the center of the box.
